Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.36,0:00:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to Essential Hayek \N 欢迎来到哈耶克简要
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.74,0:00:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Don Boudreaux \N 我是Don Boudreaux
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.24,0:00:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,professor of economics at George Mason University \N 乔治梅森大学经济学教授
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.04,0:00:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,senior fellow with the Fraser Institute \N 弗雷泽研究所高级研究员
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.22,0:00:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and blogger at Café Hayek \N 博客Café Hayek的博主之一
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.36,0:00:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This video was part of the Fraser Institute initiative \N 本视频是由弗雷泽研究所制作的
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.22,0:00:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to present the key ideas of F.A. Hayek in an easily accessible format \N 对哈耶克关键思想的通俗介绍
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.82,0:00:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,In this video, we provide an overview of Hayek's life \N 这个视频是关于哈耶克的生平、
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.50,0:00:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,his accomplishments, and the events that influenced his thinking \N 成就和影响他思想的事件
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.42,0:00:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Frederich A. Hayek was born in Vienna on May 8th, 1899 \N 弗雷德里希A.哈耶克于1899/5/8出生于维也纳
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.86,0:00:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,As a young man, he served in the Austrian army during World War I \N 年轻时他加入了奥匈帝国陆军并参加了一战
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.20,0:00:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Hayek soon found himself assigned to the Italian front \N 他被分配到了意大利前线服役
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.18,0:00:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,with his experience in combat had a profound and decisive influence on his life \N 这段战争经历给哈耶克的一生带来了深远且决定性的影响
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.72,0:00:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Following the war, Hayek returned to Vienna \N 战争结束后，哈耶克返回了维也纳
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.46,0:00:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and completed doctoral degrees in both law and political science \N 并获得了法律和政治学两个博士学位
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.20,0:01:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Working as a young economist in Austria in the late 1920s \N 1920年代后期，哈耶克作为奥地利年轻的经济学家
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.36,0:01:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hayek was taken under the wing of noted economist Ludwig von Mises \N 在知名经济学家路德维希·冯·米塞斯的羽翼下成长
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.20,0:01:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and began his work researching business cycles \N 并开始了对于经济周期的研究
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.50,0:01:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Business cycles, or what were then called trade cycles \N 经济周期，后来亦叫商业周期
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.42,0:01:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,are known today as booms and recessions \N 今天被人们称作景气和衰退
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.88,0:01:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1931, Hayek moved to England \N 1931年，哈耶克移居英国
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.72,0:01:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and joined the faculty of the London School of Economics \N 于伦敦政治经济学院任教
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.86,0:01:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,With his research into booms and recessions \N 在1930年代大萧条的背景下
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.10,0:01:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,led to his growing fame, especially against the backdrop of the Great Depression of the 1930s \N 他对于经济周期的研究，使他声望日隆 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.62,0:01:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,During this time \N 在这期间
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.84,0:01:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hayek crossed path with his greatest intellectual rival \N 哈耶克遇上了他智力上最重要的对手
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.20,0:01:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,John Maynard Keynes \N 约翰·梅纳德·凯恩斯
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.94,0:01:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,who promoted the idea that governments could actively and successfully manage the economy \N 凯恩斯推广了政府可以积极、成功地调控经济的理念
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.60,0:01:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Hayek argued in contrast \N 哈耶克则持相反观点
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.60,0:01:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that an economy is too complicated \N 他认为经济太过复杂
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.42,0:01:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and the information needed to make decisions too decentralized \N 决策所需的信息也太过分散
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.78,0:01:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,for a centrally planned economy to be efficient or effective \N 使得中央计划经济无法有效运转
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.47,0:01:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, most economists and policymakers \N 最终，大多数经济学家和政治决策者
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.30,0:02:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,embraced Keynes' view of the world and the role of government \N 选择拥抱凯恩斯对于世界和政府角色的看法
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.34,0:02:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,which came to dominate economics thinking for the next forty years \N 这一潮流延续了四十年
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.84,0:02:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hayek was largely relegated to the sidelines \N 哈耶克则在很大程度上被主流经济学界遗忘了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.34,0:02:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But Hayek's time in the shadows was brief \N 不过哈耶克并未在阴影中待太久
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.76,0:02:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1944 \N 1944年
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.76,0:02:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,he published the classic volume, <The Road to Serfdom> \N 他出版了经典之作——《通往奴役之路》
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.88,0:02:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,which became a bestseller \N 该书也成了畅销书
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.46,0:02:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1950, Hayek moved to the University of Chicago \N 1950年，哈耶克前往芝加哥大学任教
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.08,0:02:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,where he published his second major work \N 在那他出版了他的第二部重要著作
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.96,0:02:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,<The Constitution of Liberty> \N 《自由秩序原理》
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.48,0:02:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Subsequent years would see the publication of two more big thick books \N 在之后的日子里他又出版了另外两本大部头
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.94,0:02:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the three-volume <Law, Legislation and Liberty> \N 三卷本的《法律、立法与自由》
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.52,0:02:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and, in 1988, <The Fatal Conceit> \N 和1988年出版的《致命的自负》
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.28,0:02:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1974, Hayek was awarded the Nobel prize in Economics \N 1974年，哈耶克被授予诺贝尔经济学奖
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.60,0:02:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,finally earning the professional acclaim that he’d lost with his refusal to jump onto Keynesian bandwagon \N 终于重获因当年与凯恩斯意见不同而失去的专业声誉
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.72,0:02:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1991 \N 1991年
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.24,0:02:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the collapse of the Soviet Union provided further indication of Hayek's notion \N 苏联的解体为哈耶克关于
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.48,0:03:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that central planning by government simply does not, indeed, cannot, work \N 政府中央计划经济无法、也不可能运转的见解提供了新的注脚
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.24,0:03:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Readers interested in exploring Hayek's theories in greater depth \N 我们鼓励想更深入了解哈耶克理论的读者
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.48,0:03:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,are encouraged to read his works directly \N 直接阅读哈耶克的著作
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.24,0:03:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I recommend starting with <The Road to Serfdom> \N 我建议从《通往奴役之路》开始
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.98,0:03:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and economic students might wish to start with Hayek's influential 1945 essay \N 经济系学生可能会希望从哈耶克1945年那篇极富影响力的文章
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.28,0:03:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,<The Use of Knowledge in Society> \N 《知识在社会中的运用》开始
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.46,0:03:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,To learn more and to download <Essential Hayek> for free \N 想要了解更多或者下载《哈耶克简要》
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.48,0:03:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,visit www.essentialhayek.org \N 请访问www.essentialhayek.org
